# Wallet Service Context

Before implementing any change, **read the relevant docs** from `docs/`:

| Task type | Read these files |
|-----------|-----------------|
| Domain, business logic, data model | `docs/domain.md`, `docs/datamodel.md` |
| Backend, architecture, API | `docs/architecture/backend-architecture.md`, `docs/architecture/systemPatterns.md` |
| Database, migrations | `docs/architecture/database-migrations.md` |
| General | `docs/projectbrief.md` |

Project rules and conventions are in `AGENTS.md`. Do not assume; load the files and apply what they specify.

**Dependency rule**: Domain and app must not use any external third-party library. No Prisma, Pino, uuidv7, Zod in domain or app. Allowed: TypeScript stdlib, interfaces (ports), and `utils/kernel/` only. Never import from `utils/infrastructure/` or `utils/middleware/` in domain or app ‚Äî that's an architecture violation. Third-party libs live only in adapters.

**Entity IDs ‚Äî UUID v7 only, in application**: App generates IDs via `IIDGenerator`; DB never generates them. Never UUID v4.

**Amounts ‚Äî Integer cents (BigInt)**: All financial amounts are the smallest currency unit. `$1.99` = `199`. Never float, never decimal. API sends/receives `amount_cents: number`.

**Timestamps**: Unix ms everywhere ‚Äî DB (BigInt), domain, ports, DTOs, API. Single representation, no conversion.

**Queries**: Use ReadStore ports (return DTOs). Do not load aggregates for reads.

**Logging**: Use `ILogger` (port); wired as PinoAdapter ‚Üí SensitiveKeysFilter ‚Üí SafeLogger. mainLogTag per file, methodLogTag per method; every message starts with methodLogTag.

**Error handling**: Use `AppError` (Kind + Code + Message). Domain: factory functions returning `AppError`. HTTP handlers throw ‚Äî global `onError` in `index.ts` catches `AppError`, maps Kind ‚Üí HTTP status via `httpStatus()`, returns `errorResponse()` ‚Üí `{"error": "CODE", "message": "..."}`. Middleware uses `errorResponse()` directly. Every error needs a unique UPPER_SNAKE_CASE Code.

**Concurrency**: Optimistic locking (`version` field) for ALL wallet mutations including PlaceHold/VoidHold. System wallets use atomic increment (no version check). No `SELECT FOR UPDATE` in domain ports (infrastructure leak). All mutations: idempotency keys required. TransactionManager: Serializable isolation + internal retry (3 attempts, exponential backoff) before escalating `VERSION_CONFLICT` to client.

**Ledger**: Double-entry bookkeeping. Every financial op = 2 LedgerEntry records (debit + credit). `ledger_entries` is immutable (append-only): never UPDATE, never DELETE.

**API endpoints**: Auto-generated via hono-openapi + Scalar. Each endpoint folder has `schemas.ts` (Zod request + response) and `handler.ts` (describeRoute + validators + handler). Register routes in BC route files (e.g., `wallets.routes.ts`).

**Responses to user**: Always in Spanish. Code and documentation in English.
